The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Good Morning
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Good Morning
      Hello It's Sunday , April 13 , 2008                
	Fest fun    Attend the last day of Resonance 08, an annual cultural festival presented by Institute of Post Graduate Medical Education amp; Research (SSKM Hospital), t2 and IAMS, at Sarala Roy Memorial Community Hall, 9am.    
	 Pottery    Learn to make pots, pitchers, vases and other decorative terracotta items at a pottery workshop at Merlin Homeland, 12.30pm.        
	Creative writing    Take your kids to a creative writing workshop for children in the age group of 10-18 at Oxford Junior bookstore, 4pm to 6pm.         
	On stage    Enjoy Anilket Sondhya at Greenwood Spirit Theatre Festival at Madhusudan Mancha, 10.30am.        
	Eye on art    Take a look at Revelation 2008 at Birla Academy of Art and Culture, 3pm to 8pm.					  Browse through Mountain Memoirs, drawings and paintings by Rabindra Nath Bhattacharjee, at Chitrakoot Art Gallery, 3pm to 8pm.				   Drop in at India Shining India Crying, a photo exhibition by Johann Rousselot, at Bose Pacia, 11am to 7pm.				   Stop over at The Season of Discontent by Barun Chowdhury at Aakriti Art Gallery, 3pm to 7pm.                                                                                                                                                              
